cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a machine learning technique for feature extraction from time-series data, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus on intermittent time-series data and the use of time-frequency patterns suggests a potential fit for information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the evaluation of the technique on synthetic and real-world data aligns with the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE).
